<title>USA: GTE asks US court to overturn FCC phone rule.</title>
<headline>GTE asks US court to overturn FCC phone rule.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1997-06-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>GTE Corp said Friday it asked a U.S. appeals court in St. Louis to overturn the Federal Communications Commission's recent orders on access charges and price caps.</p>
<p>GTE said the orders are unlawful and should be struck down.</p>
<p>&quot;Far from being deregulatory and competitively neutral, the orders are biased against local exchange carriers,&quot; GTE spokesman Bob Bishop said.</p>
<p>He said GTE also plans to ask the court to overturn the FCC's recent order covering universal service.</p>
<p>SBC Communications Inc also has asked the same court to strike down all three orders and wants the court to suspend the rules while it considers the carrier's request.</p>
